data.meta_description:
527 likes, 7 comments - romanpilipey on June 30, 2024: "Toretsk, eastern Donetsk region, June 2024. for @afpphoto 
Part II.

For over a week I was in and out of Toretsk and its surrounding area. A mining town in the Donetsk region that compared to others in war-scarred east Ukraine was nestled in a relatively sleepy sector of the front line. Itâ€™s not anymore.

With the new Russian assault on Toretsk life there deteriorated drastically. Ukrainian forces lost some of the positions outside the town which they were holding for a long period of time. And as rockets and air strikes started raining down on shaken residents this month, many began to leave, fearing their hometown would face the same fate as other Ukrainian eastern towns that were attacked by Russia with its scorched-earth assault tactics, while others, despite all appeals to evacuate, made the decision to stay no matter what.".
